# Styling

## CSS Modules

- **Always use `.module.css`** — Colocate with components: `ComponentName.module.css`
- Import as: `import classes from './ComponentName.module.css'`
- Apply via: `className={classes.className}`

## Shared Styles

- `app/styles/root.styles.module.css` — Global styles, breadcrumb links, body
- Use `:global` sparingly for global overrides

## Mantine Integration

- Use Mantine layout props (`mt`, `mb`, `p`, `gap`, etc.) where possible
- Use CSS modules for component-specific overrides (heights, widths, layout tweaks)
- Reference Mantine vars: `var(--mantine-color-dimmed)`, `var(--mantine-h2-font-size)`, etc.

## Naming

- Class names: camelCase in modules (e.g. `videocard`, `breadcrumbLink`)
- Some modules use lowercase (e.g. `footer.module.css`, `navigation.module.css`) — prefer consistency with `ComponentName.module.css` when creating new files
